Today actor Ross Kemp launches his "Knock, name, natter" plan. He urges people to pop event invitations through neighbours' doors, and seize the chance to get talking. Daily Express polling reveals 59 percent think the Queen's service has secured the future of the monarchy. And 44 percent - backed by this newspaper - want an extra bank holiday, a "Thank Holiday", to honour her and the millions who do heroic unseen work in their communities. Boris Johnson is said to back the idea. Historian Dan Snow enthused: "This weekend is going to be historic. My kids will certainly tell their grandchildren about it." 